Toss a fair coin three times. What is the probability of getting one head and two tails?
(A) \frac{1}{2}
(B) \frac{1}{4}
(C) \frac{1}{8}
(D) \frac{3}{8}

Toss a fair coin four times. What is the probability of getting four heads?
(A) \frac{1}{4}
(B) \frac{1}{8}
(C) \frac{1}{16}
(D) \frac{3}{16}

Toss a fair coin five times. What is the probability of getting five heads?
(A) \frac{1}{5}
(B) \frac{3}{8}
(C) \frac{1}{16}
(D) \frac{1}{32}

